Title: EAMES DCW (dining chair wood).
Description:
QR Code Link to This Post

This is an early Dining Chair Wood, designed by Eames. I think it's rosewood, but I'm not sure. I also think it was a chair used at the CBS studios in NYC, since I found it about a block from the old Ed Sullivan theatre. The brass plaque underneath read CBS and a number. The shock mount on the backrest was oval, but when I sent it to Herman Miller to have it replaced, they used two circular mounts. The chair has a few condition issues, such as a patch on the seat (repaired by Prestige in Queens, who Herman Miller referred me to), and a few dings in the veneer around the perimeter - but those are to be expected from a chair of this age. In terms of hardware, the chair has the early Herman Miller 5-2-4 setup, dating it to the early 50's.
I'm asking $1,100.
